# MEMORY.md.example

This example shows the shape of durable memory if the user explicitly consents. Do not store real memory in this committed file.

## Allowed Memory

- User-stated preferences for reflection style.
- User-approved recurring values or coping strategies.
- User-approved therapy-prep preferences.

## Disallowed Memory

- Raw journal entries.
- Crisis notes.
- Unreviewed inferred traits.
- Diagnoses or suspected diagnoses.
- Secrets, credentials, or third-party private information.

## Example

- Reflection preference: The user prefers concise summaries with one optional next step.
- Coping preference: The user finds grounding prompts more useful than cognitive reframes during high stress.
